---
title: Honey Mustard Chicken with Roasted Sweet Potatoes, Zucchini, and Onion
description: In this recipe, we’re DIY-ing our way to a honey mustard sauce that's leagues better than the bottled stuff—add in a pinch of garlic and a splash of white wine vinegar and boom! You've got it made. Here, we’re reducing it into a satisfying sticky glaze for chicken breasts. With roasted zucchini, sweet potatoes, and red onion to fill it out, it’s a symphony of sweet and savory.
